parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended sudden acceleration can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may accelerate rapidly without the driver's intention or input.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without warning
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the driver must stand on the brakes to stop the vehicle
the vehicle may crash into objects or other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hardness of the brake pedal can cause difficulty in stopping the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries. In extreme cases, the pedal can go to the floor, resulting in a complete loss of braking ability.
symptoms: The brake pedal is very hard to press
the brake pedal goes straight to the floorboard

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion and Freezing of Brake Caliper Pins and Rotors
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and freezing of brake caliper pins and rotors can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: Brake caliper pins and rotors are frozen and rusted

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion-related failure of the front cradle or subframe can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Unusual noises or vibrations from the front of the vehicle
and potentially a sudden loss of control or collapse of the front suspension.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, pose a risk to the driver and passengers, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine bursts into flames while driving
smoke or flames visible from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. Repeated engine replacements can indicate a systemic problem with the engine design or manufacturing process.
symptoms: engine catching on fire after replacement.
